         <abstract>
            <p>Every fall the Department of Commerce makes sales projections for several hundred industries. Although these forecasts are based in part on the judgment of industry specialists, they also depend on regression studies of the sensitivity of industry sales to GNP fluctuations. These studies identify the most sensitive and least sensitive industries, separate out of historical industry growth trends the growth that is merely response to growth in GNP, and provide an algebraic link between GNP forecasts and future industry sales.</p>
          </abstract>
